  "body": {
    "title": "Hard Fork to Protocol Version 11 (\"van Rossem\" Hard Fork)",
    "abstract": "Example hard-fork-initiation governance action moving the network from major protocol version 10 to major protocol version 11. Used to illustrate the schema; not a real anchor.",
    "motivation": "Demonstrate the wire-shape of a CIP-116 hard_fork_initiation_action embedded inside CIP-108 metadata, with the previous hard-fork action referenced in `gov_action_id` and the target version in `protocol_version`.",
    "rationale": "Following the schema, the on-chain payload binds the proposal text to a specific (previous-action, target-version) tuple, providing replay protection: a malicious actor cannot reuse this metadata against a different hard-fork target without the document hash diverging.",
    "references": [
      {
        "@type": "Other",
        "label": "CIP-1694 | A First Step Towards On-Chain Decentralized Governance",
        "uri": "https://github.com/cardano-foundation/CIPs/tree/master/CIP-1694"
      },
      {
        "@type": "Other",
        "label": "CIP-0116 | Universal JSON Encoding for Domain Types",
        "uri": "https://github.com/cardano-foundation/CIPs/tree/master/CIP-0116"
      }
    ],
